      • connect

        public static boolean connect(java.lang.String[][] a,
                              java.lang.String[][] b)
        Connects two cube pieces and places them into the 2D array called combine. This method checks pieces by looking at String [][] a's top, bottom, left, and right areas with String[][] b . If a pairing is found that the two pieces are combined and placed within String[][] combine.
        Parameters:
        String[][] - a, String[][] b Accepts two cube fragments. 　@return boolean con If a pairing is found con is return true.

      • confirmtop

        public static boolean confirmtop(java.lang.String[][] a,
                                 java.lang.String[][] b)
        Checks to see if a top pairing can be found. This means that String [][]a's bottom most array is compared with String[][]b's upper most array. If the integer called pair reaches the same number as the length of String[][]b then there is a pairing.
        Parameters:
        String[][] - a, String[][] b Accepts two cube fragments. 　@return boolean con Returns true if there is a pairing
